                    <msContents>
                        <summary><title type="uniform">Kristinréttur Árna biskups</title></summary>
                        <titlePage type="ms">
                            <docTitle>
                                <titlePart type="main">Christinn Rettur <lb/> Nye <lb/> Edur <lb/>
                                    Arna Biskups <lb/> Samanskrifadur <lb/> Anno 1274 <lb/> enn
                                    <lb/> Logtekinn a ISLANDE <lb/> Anno 1275: (<locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus>) </titlePart>
                            </docTitle>
                        </titlePage>
                        <msItem n="1" class="klog">
                            <locus from="1r" to="70v">1r-70v (pp. 1-139)</locus>
                            <title type="uniform">Kristinréttur Árna biskups</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="is"/>
                            <rubric>Christen Rettr Arna b. <lb/> 1 Cap: <lb/> Hversu med barn skal
                                fara til skírnar.</rubric>
                            <incipit>Ala skal barn hvert er borit verdr, a man<ex>n</ex>z <lb/>
                                Hofut er á</incipit>
                            <explicit>ok skal þat hafa kóngr enn hálfr byscop</explicit>
                            <note>The text is divided into 32 numbered chapters followed by three
                                unnumbered chapters.</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="chart">
                                <support><material>Paper</material>. <watermark>Watermarks: Pro Patria (Maid of Dort).
                                    Countermark: the crowned initials
                                    "GR".</watermark></support>
                                <extent>iii + 71 leaves. Size of leaves: <dimensions type="leaf" scope="all" unit="mm">
                                    <height>161</height>
                                    <width>101</width>
                                </dimensions>. The first flyleaf is an endpaper. The following
                                    two flyleaves are conjoint and stuck to the first quire. </extent>
                                <foliation><p>Pagination 1-139. The pagination starts on f. <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>. F. <locus from="71r" to="71v">71r-v</locus> is blank and not
                                    paginated.</p></foliation>
                                <collation><p/>
                                    <signatures>There are quire signatures from A to I.</signatures>
                                    <catchwords>There are no catchwords.</catchwords>
                                </collation>
                                <condition><p>The manuscript is in good condition.</p></condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="23 24">
                                    <p>Long lines with 23-24 lines per page. The text is written
                                        exclusively on the verso sides of the leaves and rectos are
                                        left blank. F. <locus from="71r" to="71v">71r-v</locus> is
                                        blank too.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc hands="1">
                            <handNote scribe="unknown" scope="sole" script="humcursiva">
                                <p> Written in one hand.</p>
                                <p>The hand is similar to the hand of <name type="person" key="ThoSig007">Þorkell Sigurðsson</name> from the first
                                    part of <ref xml:id="AM02-0395-is">AM 395 fol.</ref>; therefore
                                    the manuscript could be dated to the middle of the eighteenth
                                    century.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote>No decorations. </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>On the <locus from="FFL-002r" to="FFL-002r">second flyleaf</locus>,
                                a commentary in Danish with the heading: <q>Notia
                                    Exemplaris</q>, starting: <q>Dette Exemplar er skrevet effter et
                                        andet <unclear>ehsst</unclear> Exemplar <lb/> paa Charta,
                                        hvilket er den 179 Num: in 4to paa Universi<lb/>tetets
                                        Bibliotheqve...</q> is found.</p>
                            <p>The recto side of the <locus from="FFL-003r" to="FFL-003r">third
                                flyleaf</locus> is blank but on the <locus from="FFL-003v" to="FFL-003v">verso side</locus> there are some provenance
                                notes: <list>
                                    <item><q>Luxdorph</q></item>
                                    <item><q>Schaldemose 1816</q></item>
                                    <item><q>1818 foræret Nykjóbings Kathedraskole af Hr. Adj.
                                        Schaldemose.</q></item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1750" notAfter="1788" cert="medium" evidence="conjecture" resp="KatKap001">
                            <p>Probably written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in
                                <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1788">the second half of
                                    the eighteenth century</origDate>.</p>
                            <p>If the identification of the hand is correct the manuscript must be
                                written in the second half of the eighteenth century, as <name type="person" key="ThoSig007">Þorkell Sigurðsson</name> was born
                                in 1724.</p>
                            <p>If the signature on the <locus from="FFL-003v" to="FFL-003v">verso
                                side of the third flyleaf</locus> is <name type="person" key="BolLux001">Bolle Willum Luxdorph's</name>, then the
                                manuscript must have left Iceland before Luxdorph's death in <date when="1788">1788</date>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscripts <ref target="#Acc-0051-en #Acc-0052-en #Acc-0053-en #Acc-0054-en #Acc-0056-en #Acc-0057-en                                  #Acc-0058-en #Acc-0059-en #Acc-0060-en #Acc-0061-en #Acc-0062-en">Acc. 51-62</ref> belong to the collection of manuscripts
                                Frederik Schaldemose bequeathed to <name type="org">Nykøbing
                                    Katedralskole</name>. Most of them are Fredrik Schaldemose's
                                transcriptions of Old Norse texts.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p><orgName key="AMS">The Arnamagnæan Collection</orgName> in <name type="place" key="Copen01">Copenhagen</name> acquired the
                                manuscript from the school in <date when="2007">April 2007</date> as
                                a gift.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
